to give you some drama

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:56.240
You're not writing this. Do you get that?

00:04:56.240 --> 00:05:00.440
Okay. Okay. You're right.

00:05:18.660 --> 00:05:20.190
You know

00:05:20.190 --> 00:05:23.830
for a while I felt the same way. I think
we all do.

00:05:25.890 --> 00:05:28.890
We all want a story.

00:05:30.910 --> 00:05:37.710
We want that perfect resolution to our
heartaches and curiosity.

00:05:38.540 --> 00:05:40.620
But this isn't a story.

00:05:41.710 --> 00:05:47.500
So you need to stop thinking about us
like you can predict or control

00:05:47.500 --> 00:05:49.520
where we're going.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:53.760
So you're not curious about us anymore?

00:05:54.460 --> 00:05:55.040
No.

00:05:56.409 --> 00:06:05.349
Fuck. I mean- Yes. But I'm not going to
keep sabotaging my reality for the sake

00:06:05.349 --> 00:06:07.149
of fiction.

00:06:07.149 --> 00:06:12.349
That's what you do. That's what you did the
whole time we were together.

00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:15.180
Because in your head

00:06:15.189 --> 00:06:18.249
real life is never as good as a story.

00:06:18.249 --> 00:06:21.339
You don't actually want me, Evan.

00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:27.579
You want the possibility of me. You
always want me as a destination.

00:06:28.060 --> 00:06:31.920
But, I don't think you actually want to get
there.

00:06:33.340 --> 00:06:34.920
I'm not certain that's true anymore.

00:06:36.459 --> 00:06:39.459
But you're not certain it's not to true either.

00:06:40.930 --> 00:06:46.450
And... that's no foundation to build a relationship on.

00:06:48.260 --> 00:06:50.800
You gotta be honest with yourself.

00:06:52.280 --> 00:06:53.240
With me.

00:06:55.040 --> 00:07:01.700
You know, it took me a while to accept it
and it fucking sucked. But I get it now.

00:07:03.810 --> 00:07:09.250
And I'm in a good place and you need to get
there too.

00:07:11.260 --> 00:07:14.040
I mean, you say you want this story

00:07:14.300 --> 00:07:17.180
but you've been stuck on this one page
this whole time

00:07:18.480 --> 00:07:21.800
No story can happen if you're not
willing to turn the page

00:07:22.520 --> 00:07:27.500
You're holding on to this one moment or
possibility and before you know it the

00:07:27.510 --> 00:07:33.840
rest of the world is going to finish
reading the book and start reading new

00:07:33.840 --> 00:07:38.250
ones and you're going to be stuck here
reading the same page over and over.

00:07:42.840 --> 00:07:45.140
You can't be so scared, Evan.

00:07:46.580 --> 00:07:48.100
I mean, it's you and me.

00:07:50.400 --> 00:07:54.200
It's you and me. You don't think that I don't know what
that means?

00:07:56.240 --> 00:07:58.940
It won't be the same thing as time goes on though.

00:07:59.180 --> 00:08:07.220
And it shouldn't. It should evolve and even fade a little.

00:08:07.620 --> 00:08:10.800
But there are certain things that will never
disappear.

00:08:12.380 --> 00:08:14.520
Those things are untouchable.

00:08:15.740 --> 00:08:19.130
You, Evan, are untouchable.

00:08:20.080 --> 00:08:24.720
The people were, at that time in
our lives

00:08:25.970 --> 00:08:28.470
It's untouchable.

00:08:34.940 --> 00:08:36.820
I'll see you around.

00:08:38.780 --> 00:08:39.520
Yeah.

